Oh, and on occassion, compensate the Chanter, <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  too...especially if they've been casting Rune...which require the same dots.  I can't even begin to count all the times that those runes have saved my cleric's life.<br>
<br>
Pre-Seb bites but Post-Seb makes up for all those items you've had to sell to buy your dots in the past.  Even the newly revamped Chardok is droppin' more gems.<br>
<br>
The suggestion to have a chanter buy your dots is good, however, keeping a set of Cha gear on you, as well, works wonders. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  140 Cha (I believe) is max Cha which knocks the price down from 12plat to 10.5plat...which is the least I've been able to buy them for at 200 Cha.<br>
<br>
Welp, that was my 2 copper...hope it helps! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
