</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarwinianseafarer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darwinian Seafarer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/15/01 6:35:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Money comes and goes..<br>
Sometimes you'll find you're paying out up to 2k a week for Peri's.. Other times you'll find you're up 2k from slight overcompensations.<br>
<br>
There tends to be a rather strong myth that all Clerics ML and keep much more then they need.. So I prefer to not ML, though when I do, I make certain I'm breaking even or just slightly under/over.<br>
<br>
For the record.. In HoT and Fear, if it's more or less an open raid, you can expect to foot a good portion of the Peridot bill. That's just a generalization, though.. <br>
<br>
I always carry 60+ Peridots on me.. Restock when I get under 20.. Although I occasionally forget and have to get the elusive TL to WC to pick up more after binding hastily at whatever location I'm at.. heh.<br>
<br>
But, if all else fails, and you're flat broke with 0 Peridots (which does happen more often then I'd care to remember) you can always whine to every single person you know. *grin* Someone is bound to toss a few hundred plat your way. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And whoever mentioned whoring out Leo.. Good idea.. Cept he smells like Bard, so you may have to fix the odor.<br>
